----------------------------Required Prerequisites:----------------------------------

		Windows or Mac Computer 
		Reasonably Fast / Consistent Wifi
		Functioning Robinhood Account
		Robinhood Account must be margin (not cash)
		
			- No daytrade ban
			- Day trades are at 0
		
		
----------------------------Recommended Prerequisites:-------------------------------

		Robinhood account has 2 factor authentication.

---------------------------General Info ---------------------------------------------

        Any text in the Terminal / Command Prompt Program that is white is good, red
	text are usually errors. If red text appears: end process, take screenshot, and
	send to Alexei. 

	All commands in this document are separated with distinct spacing. 
	Type them EXACTLY as provided only modifying if specified. Same thing goes for the
	prompts in the command area. It is case sensetive and type exactly as instructed.

	Setup instruction assume user has no programming experience.
	
	If you would like to terminate a command, press control - c. This, however, doesn't
	end the main program once it has began, instead the program continues, but the command
	program lets you type new commands.
	
	When you answer a prompt or run a command, pressing enter essentially "begins" the process,
	if you don't press enter, similar to how you send a message to someone.
	
	All times listed in the tutorial are listed in US Eastern Time, (time in New York where 
	the markets the program trades on are located). Depending on your location, you can expect
	the program to run at different parts of the day, i.e. US Pacific Time --> program begins
	at 6:00 a.m. and ends at 8:30 a.m.
	
	Preferred method of Contact: alexei.tryshev@gmail.com


---------------------------Security---------------------------------------------

	The program prompts for the Email and Password. The Email and Password
are stored in an encrypted CSV file. This makes the process more secure. Life is just better
if you have 2 Factor Authentication.

	It is worthy to mention that the program will on occasion lose money, and this should be expected as there
is always risk involved in the stock market. I am no way responsible for any loss of money. If there has
been a consistent trend in a loss of money, please contact me for investigation.

--------------------------- Setup ---------------------------------------------------


1. Go to https://git-scm.com/download/win (will start download immediately) and download the latest version of “Git”.
	a. If mac →   https://git-scm.com/download/win
	
2. Installation for Windows:
	-Leave everything else as default except: 
	-Choose this C:\Program Files\Git
	-Choose the "Use native secure file ... "
	-Also check "Use Windows Default console window" 
	

2. Go to https://heroku.com/ and sign up for a free account.

3.  Go to https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-python#set-up and download the 
appropriate version of the Heroku CLI.

4. Instllation for Heroku for Windows:
	-Leave everything as default except: 
	-directory: C:\Program Files(x86)\heroku

4. Open “Command Prompt Program” (press control - shift - esc. Click run
new task, and type in "cmd" (no quotations), select run with administrative
 privileges and press enter) on your computer  if you have Windows. For Mac 
open “Terminal” app.

5. In your command area run   git config --global user.name "Bob Random"   Where Bob Random would be replaced with the username bound to your 
computer. Keep quotation marks when running this command.)

6. Run this command   git config --global user.email “bobrandom@gmail.com"   (Where the email address is replaced with your preferred email. 
Keep quotation marks when typing command)

7. Run this command   heroku login   (or      heroku login -i      if that doesn't work). Next, press any key and this will open a 
browser tab. If you ran the second command, you will login in the command area.

8. If it says heroku isn't a valid command (usually a problem with Windows), roceed to locate the Heroku application in your
file explorer, right click --> Preferences at the top there should be a tab with "Compatability" and check mark where it says
“Run with compatibility...”. Return to command area and rerun      heroku login  


9. Next you will create a heroku app, type in the following commands one by one and press enter after each. (replace appname 
with you actual appname)

	heroku create appname     ( in this scenario appname is replaced with the preferred name, Heroku may not accept the
	provided name. In this case, rerun the command with a different appname satisfying the requirements.)
	
	mkdir appname     (for Windows) or sudo mkdir appname (for Mac)
	
	cd appname
	
	git init	

10. Run the command    python    in the Terminal and press enter. If there are 3 consecutive right arrows and the version 
is greater than 2.7, skip step 4 and 5, close the terminal and open it back up. Next type cd appname into the Command area 
and press enter.

11. If you determined that your version of python is lower than 3, the next step is still needed
And type     python3     in all following commands that feature python. 

12. If you are met with an error from the previous step, follow the Python installation tutorial:
	a. Go to https://www.python.org/downloads/ and download Python 3.8.2 (not the most recent version). 
	
	b. Open the Launcher inside of the download Folder (should be an .exe file type
	or .dmg for Mac.). 
	c. Right click the installer and run as administrator. then select these options:
		-add python 3.8.2 to PATH
		-customize installation
		-associate files with python (check this)
		-Make sure you install Python to C:\Program Files (x86)\Python\Python32\
	

13. Proceed to find the app in the File Explorer (or Finder) and transfer it over to the last possible 
subfolder of the Python installation. When you move it, it might say that it can't because the folder is open. If so,
close the command program and try transferring again. The directory should end up looking something like 
this: .../.../Python/Python32/app_name

14. Return to the Terminal / Command Prompt Program (control - shift - e then run new task with cmd and adminstratitve rights,
like before if you have Windows).

15. Run       git remote add heroku https://git.heroku.com/appname.git       (where appname is replaced with your real
appname)

16. Run this command          git clone https://github.com/AlexeiT497/StockProgram.git

17. Switch from Command area to the files area, find your application folder (search for the name of your application).

18. Inside, there should be a sub-folder called, "StockProgram", it contains around 25 files. 
Transfer everything from the StockProgram folder into the outer application folder. 

19. The StockProgram folder should be empty, and everything should be in the outer application folder. 
You may delete the StockProgram folder.

20. Run this command      pip3 install -r requirements.txt 
	- if that command did not work try        pip install -r requirements.txt

21. Run     python preferences.py     and answer the prompts, be careful to enter info correctly. If you made a mistake, 
press control - c and rerun         python preferences.py       .
	- For the fraction prompt enter as a number between 1 and 0, 1 being 100% of the account. For example, if you had
	$50 in stocks and $50 in cash, the max digit you may enter is 0.5, anything larger would overlap with non-usable stock
	cash.
	
	- For the fraction secontion, I would recommend only investing $10 on the first day just to check the program.
	After you are confident to inveset more, rerun       python preferences.py       to change your preferences.

22. 
	a. Run     python Authentication.py 
	b. Probably, it will prompt you for some sort of code on the first run. Enter that code (try no spaces first for the code, 
	if it doesn't work, do it with spaces) and press enter. 

23. Finally, you are ready to start the application. Enter   python begin.py   and press enter. This will run several commands.
	
24. After this, it should open a new Chrome tab with an error message. Not a real error message, and close it.

25. The program should be working. It will continue to work even if you turn off computer.
II would recommend to keep the Terminal / cmd.exe with the program open if you would like to enter commands.

26. To end the program run     python end.py      .

----------------------------------General Usage---------------------------------------------------------

1. During the evening, run    python Authentication.py     and if it runs with no prompts, cool. If it does prompt, 
enter code. Additionally run       heroku login      (or     heroku login -i      ) and re-run     python begin.py     . 

2. From here on, the program will always be on (unless you enter     python end.py     ). Usually the program will display 
something like  "16:55 Will continue checking...", every 20 seconds. Even if the time logged doesn't match the time in your 
location this is normal, ignore it.
 
 3. If the program displays something like "
2020-05-14T13:30:16.917543+00:00 app[worker.1]: login = r.login(email, password)
2020-05-14T13:30:16.917548+00:00 app[worker.1]: File "/app/robin_stocks/authentication.py", line 124, in login
2020-05-14T13:30:16.917707+00:00 app[worker.1]: EOFError: EOF when reading a line" . Then press control - c.
Run        python Authentication.py       . Then answer the 2 factor authentication prompt. Then run     python begin.py    .
When this happens, it will not buy any stocks today.

4. The program will buy stocks from 9:30 a.m. to around 10:30 a.m. (US Eastern Time). You can expect that it will buy
1 day trade stock (beginning from 9:31 a.m.), and 1:30 hours later is will buy 3 (1/3 of the budget for each) 
full-day stock (it will sell this the next day) at 9:00, don't worry it takes  Pattern Day Trade rule into account. 
The program will still buy full-day stocks even if the account is out of day trades.  If the program
does anything strange (e.g. not buy something, or weird code-like errors), press control c and run     python end.py    . 
This will end the process. Take a screenshot and send it to me for investiagtion.

5. Because of how the program works, all pending order submitted by user (not the program), will probably be cancelled, so 
watch out with your order between 9:00 and 10:30 a.m.

6. When buying, the program may submit a buy order, cancel order, and buy again, this is normal.

7. Everyday, after 10:30 a.m. , run this command    python updatecsv.py   ( or     python UpdateCSV.py      if other doesn't
work). This is very important because it will regulate your day trades. It will also prompt you to enter the full day stock 
that the program bought.

8. Also rerun the program by after updating csv by entering this command       python begin.py      .

9. When the program decides which stock to buy, it might display something like "Robinhood Client Error: ...", this is 
normal and it is not a real error.

10. You make look around through the files, however, it is not recommended to edit anything, this may result in a catastrophic 
failure.

11. If you would like to change preferences, rerun           python preferences.py              and also rerun 
      python begin.py                      in order to restart the application with new information.
